            </existDates>
            <biogHist>
                <p>Mary was one of twin daughters born to Donald Ferguson, crofter, and Marion
                    Ferguson née Campbell. There were a further five daughters two sons in the
                    family. Initially Mary worked as a domestic servant in the family home. After
                    her father's death, she is listed as living alone with her mother in the 1861
                    census. By the time of the 1871 census, she is to be found living with her much
                    younger brother John and his niece Marion in Cladach a' Baile Shear, North Uist;
                    she lived with her brother, who is listed variously as an agricultural labourer,
                    worker and fisherman, until 1909. </p>
                <p>Mary died in 1909, unmarried and a pauper, and the cause of death recorded was
                    chronic bronchitis and her brother John signed the certificate. </p>
